scrm
------------------------------------------
scrm is a coalescent simulator for biological sequences. Different to similar
programs, it can approximate the Ancestral Recombination Graph as closely as
needed, but still has only linear runtime cost for long sequences. It allows
you to rapidly simulate chromosome scale sequences with essentially correct
genetic linkage.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.5-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  libstdc++6-9.3.0-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://scrm.github.io/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/scrm/scrm/releases/download/v1.7.4/scrm-src.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack scrm-1.7.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./scrm-1.7.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/scrm-1.7.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/scrm-1.7.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(scrm)
  /usr/bin/scrm.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/scrm.README
  /usr/share/doc/scrm/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/scrm/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/scrm/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/scrm/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/scrm.1.gz

